{
  "stem": "71.4",
  "chunk_idx": 9,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "My daughter was a banker, manager, and vice president of-- of a bank.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "She raised three-- she raises three beautiful sons who attend the Sinai Day School.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And it's nice to come on Friday and have a Shabbat dinner with them.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "We have a wonderful son-in-law who makes the prayers and teaches the children and helps them with their Hebrew.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "He studied in Technion in Israel.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And he finished [INAUDIBLE], and he's making a great father and a very good husband.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And our son is married to a lovely lady, Connie.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And I hope when this tape comes out, that they will already have a little baby on their own.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And we just hope that we gave our children the best of us that we could give them, that we raised them as good Jews.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "My children-- our children were in Israel.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "We took them.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "The first time we took both of them, although Estelle was a teenager, and she rebelled.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And she said she wants to go on her own.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "But when I confronted her, I said, Estelle, for 20 years, Daddy and I want to go to Israel, and not only the money but the time could not-- did not allow us.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "We were just moving the business, and we could not leave it.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And now we decided to go, and it's going to be the greatest, greatest joy for your father to stay at the Kotel and we all four take a picture there.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "And this will be a memory for life for us.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "And she says, no, I don't want to go.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "But an hour later, she came back, and she says, Mom, you're right.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "We are going to go, and Noah came over and kissed me and says, Mommy, we will go together.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
